<sampleBrowser:SimpleFlowDocument
	xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
	xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
	xmlns:sampleBrowser="clr-namespace:ActiproSoftware.SampleBrowser"
	xmlns:shared="http://schemas.actiprosoftware.com/winfx/xaml/shared"
	>

	<Paragraph TextAlignment="Center">
		<sampleBrowser:ScreenshotControl>
			<sampleBrowser:ScreenshotControl.ImageSource>
				<BitmapImage UriSource="/Images/Screenshots/Themes-WindowChromeProcessingOverlay-200x150.png" shared:ImageProvider.CanAdapt="False" />
			</sampleBrowser:ScreenshotControl.ImageSource>
		</sampleBrowser:ScreenshotControl>
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		WindowChrome has a built-in overlay mechanism that lets you display any content above (in z-order) 
		the window's title bar and normal content areas.
		This allows for easy creation of processing screens.
	</Paragraph>

	<Paragraph>
		Press the 'Start Processing' button on this sample's window to start faux processing in a
		worker thread that lasts several seconds.  While the processing occurs, an overlay
		is displayed with a progress spinner.
	</Paragraph>

	<sampleBrowser:ExternalSampleLauncherUIContainer />

</sampleBrowser:SimpleFlowDocument>